F.7.9. MAINTENANCE â€“ MA
Tailoring Considerations for the Maintenance Family
The automated mechanisms used to schedule, conduct, and document maintenance and repairs
are not necessarily part of or connected to the OT.
When the OT cannot support the specific maintenance requirements of a control, the
organization employs compensating controls in accordance with the general tailoring guidance.
Examples of compensating controls are given with each control as appropriate.
MA-1    POLICY AND PROCEDURES

                                                                           CONTROL BASELINES
  CNTL                        CONTROL NAME
   NO.                     Control Enhancement Name
                                                                         LOW         MOD         HIGH

 MA-1       Policy and Procedures                                       Select     Select      Select

OT Discussion: The policy specifically addresses the unique properties and requirements of OT
and the relationship to non-OT systems.
